ome%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.sallybeauty.com%252Fclippers-and-beard-trimmers%252Fcordless-magic-clip%252FSBS-785225.html%253Futm_source%253Dgoogle%2526amp%253Butm_medium%253Dcpc%2526amp%253Badpos%253D%2526amp%253Bscid%253DscplpSBS-785225%2526amp%253Bsc_intid%253DSBS-785225%2526amp%253Butm_content%253DSBS-785225%2526amp%253Bgclid%253DEAIaIQobChMIzvzNrIvt6AIVxJ6zCh2hGwIrEAQYASABEgKD1_D_BwE%2526amp%253Bgclsrc%253Daw.ds%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWahl%20Magic%20Clip%20Clippers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0because%20they're%20professional-grade%2C%20wireless%2C%20and%20come%20with%20guard%20attachments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E2.%20Fading%2Ftapering%20and%20blending%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20with%20short%20haircuts%20have%20some%20form%20of%20fading%20or%20tapering%20on%20the%20back%20and%20sides%20of%20their%20heads.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20style%20of%20fade%20or%20taper%2C%20properly%20blending%20the%20hair%20is%20imperative%20to%20avoid%20a%20%26quot%3Bbowl%20cut%26quot%3B%20look.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20doing%20a%20fade%2C%20you%20want%20to%20first%20start%20by%20cutting%20with%20a%20longer%20length.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20fade%20your%20sides%20down%20to%20a%202%2C%20start%20by%20using%20a%205%20or%206%20guard.%20Then%20use%20the%202%20guard%20to%20the%20desired%20height%20depending%20on%20your%20style%20preference%20(if%20you%20want%20to%20do%20a%20high%2C%20mid%2C%20or%20low%20fade).%20Using%20a%20longer%20length%20first%20allows%20you%20to%20make%20sure%20the%202%20is%20creating%20a%20clean%20and%20visible%20line%20to%20fade%20out.%20It%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20cut%20the%20hair%20off%20cleanly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E3.%20Edging%20up%20the%20hairline%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20style%20or%20length%20you%20like%20to%20wear%20your%20hair%2C%20a%20sharp%20line%20can%20clean%20up%20your%20appearance.%20Keep%20a%20steady%20hand%20and%20follow%20the%20natural%20lines%20of%20your%20hair%2C%20and%20just%20clean%20up%20the%20stragglers.%20You%20can%20use%20the%20clippers%20you%20have%20on-hand%20to%20do%20this%2C%20but%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20clippers%20specifically%20for%20line%20ups%2C%20we%20recommend%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fthe-best-hair-clippers%23the-best-for-detailing-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndis%20Outliner%20II%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-electric-razor%23the-best-professional-razor-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndis%20T-Outliner%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EFrequently%20Asked%20Questions%20answered%20by%20a%20professional%20barber%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EShould%20I%20cut%20with%20the%20grain%20or%20against%20the%20grain%20of%20my%20hair%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20out%2C%20you%20should%20cut%20against%20the%20natural%20grain%20of%20the%20hair%20as%20it%20is%20the%20most%20effective%20way.%20If%20you%20are%20only%20cutting%20the%20sides%20and%20back%20with%20the%20clipper%2C%20just%20go%20against%20the%20grain%2C%20but%20go%20over%20it%20a%20few%20times%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20even.%20For%20people%20with%20curly%20hair%2C%20you%20should%20go%20both%20with%20and%20against%20the%20grain.%20If%20someone%20is%20giving%20themselves%20a%20complete%20buzz%20cut%2C%20I%20suggest%20they%20go%20against%20the%20grain%20everywhere%20(top%20and%20sides)%20and%20then%20with%20the%20grain%20everywhere%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20even.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20cutting%20my%20own%20hair%20with%20no%20help.%20What's%20the%20best%20way%20to%20cut%20the%20hard-to-see%20areas%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20is%20cutting%20their%20own%20hair%20I%20suggest%2C%20if%20possible%2C%20doing%20a%20double%20mirror%20technique%2C%20so%20they%20can%20see%20the%20back%20and%20sides%20better.%20If%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20second%20mirror%20on-hand%2C%20you%20can%20also%20use%20the%20selfie%20camera%20on%20your%20phone%20for%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20addition%20to%20clippers%2C%20what%20else%20should%20I%20have%20on-hand%20while%20cutting%20hair%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBarbers%20usually%20have%20an%20array%20of%20extra%20tools%20to%20use%20at%20their%20convenience%2C%20and%20you%20can%20likely%20collect%20similar%20items%20from%20around%20your%20home%3A%20Combs%20and%20hairbrushes%20for%20making%20sure%20the%20hair%20is%20laying%20properly%2C%20hair%20clips%20for%20keeping%20long%20hairs%20out%20of%20the%20way%20while%20fading%20or%20lining%20up%2C%20and%20a%20brush%20to%20clean%20up%20cut%20hair%20along%20the%20neckline%20are%20all%20useful.%20Most%20people%20don't%20have%20barber%20capes%20at%20home%2C%20but%20a%20towel%20or%20an%20old%20sheet%20can%20make%20cleaning%20up%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EUsing%20other%20resources%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20reading%20this%20how-to%20(or%20any%20other%20guide%20online)%20won't%20automatically%20give%20you%20the%20skills%20that%20professional%20barbers%20have%20gained%20from%20years%20of%20cutting%20hair%2C%20but%20there%20is%20%3Cem%3Etons%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20useful%20information%20online%20that%20can%20help%20you%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20guide%20to%20a%20specific%20haircut%20style%2C%20best%20practices%20for%20cutting%20your%20hair%20texture%2C%20or%20visual%20aid%20for%20techniques%20like%20fading%2C%20you'll%20likely%20find%20it%20on%20YouTube.%20There%20are%20plenty%20of%20professional%20barbers%2C%20hairstylists%2C%20and%20everyday%20people